# Face Recognition Model (Core Only)

This project implements the core face embedding pipeline from the PRD:

- Train a model that maps a face image to an embedding vector.
- Same identity embeddings should be close.
- Different identity embeddings should be far.

Current scope:

- Training on VGGFace2-style folder data (`train/`, `val/`).
- Backbones: ResNet-50 or MobileNetV2.
- Embedding dimensions: 128 or 512.
- Losses: ArcFace (default) or Triplet Loss.
- Mixed precision training on CUDA.
- Minimal similarity validation on validation identities.
- Inference utilities for image to embedding and gallery matching.

## Dataset Layout

Expected folder layout:

data/
  train/
    person_0001/
      img1.jpg
      img2.jpg
    person_0002/
      ...
  val/
    person_0001/
      ...
    person_0002/
      ...

## Install

1. Create/activate a Python environment.
2. Install dependencies:

   pip install -r requirements.txt

## Train

Example:

python -m face_model_core.cli train \
  --data-root ./data \
  --backbone resnet50 \
  --embedding-dim 512 \
  --loss-type arcface \
  --epochs 12 \
  --batch-size 32 \
  --learning-rate 1e-3 \
  --checkpoint-dir ./checkpoints

## Build Gallery

python -m face_model_core.cli build-gallery \
  --gallery-root ./data/val \
  --checkpoint ./checkpoints/best.pt \
  --output ./artifacts/gallery.npz

## Infer

python -m face_model_core.cli infer \
  --image ./sample.jpg \
  --checkpoint ./checkpoints/best.pt \
  --gallery ./artifacts/gallery.npz \
  --threshold 0.4

## Output Artifacts

- Model checkpoints: `.pt`
- Optional gallery embeddings: `.npz`

## Notes

- For slower environments, reduce image size to 112 and use MobileNetV2.
- Save checkpoints regularly when using Colab.
- This repo intentionally excludes large-scale benchmarking and deployment.
